00:34:54,519 --> 00:34:58,307
I think it's going to get more and
more exciting, the Championship.

481
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:01,159
Is it possible to be equal in the Championship?

482
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,268
-No.
-Shit.

483
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,476
There can be only one winner.

484
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:12,476
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
30th OCTOBER 1988

485
00:35:20,119 --> 00:35:22,679
It is the fifteenth Grand Prix of the season.

486
00:35:23,239 --> 00:35:25,833
As the sun rises, Brazil will await the chequered flag

487
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:30,675
and for Ayrton Senna to win
his first world title in Formula One,

488
00:35:31,159 --> 00:35:34,994
realising a dream he had
since he was a child.

489
00:35:39,719 --> 00:35:40,994
The pressure was a matter.

490
00:35:41,119 --> 00:35:42,155
VOICE OF PIERRE VAN VILET
TF1 COMMENTATOR

