normally he could not overtake.

725
00:52:35,039 --> 00:52:40,909
But I said to Ron and Ayrton,
two or three races before Suzuka

726
00:52:41,280 --> 00:52:45,512
because every time Ayrton,
tried, especially at the start, to overtake me,

727
00:52:45,639 --> 00:52:48,438
I open the door, because I do not want to have a crash.

728
00:52:48,559 --> 00:52:49,548
I said to them:

729
00:52:49,639 --> 00:52:53,871
"From now on, no way I will open the door, anymore

730
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:58,032
"We are fighting as ourselves, I don't care of the
team spirit.

731
00:52:58,119 --> 00:53:00,110
"I will fight for myself."

732
00:53:04,519 --> 00:53:06,032
The Championship is neck to neck.

733
00:53:06,199 --> 00:53:07,393
VOICE OF JOHN BISIGNANO
ESPN COMMENTATOR

734
00:53:07,519 --> 00:53:10,478
Senna has to win
the Japanese Grand Prix

735
00:53:10,559 --> 00:53:14,108
to keep the points battle going on till the last race.

736
00:53:15,239 --> 00:53:21,429
Prost knows, that if Senna does not finish, he will be the Formula One champion.

737
00:53:24,119 --> 00:53:28,237
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
22nd OCTOBER 1989

738
00:53:37,559 --> 00:53:39,277
On-board Camera of
Ayrton Senna

739
00:53:40,719 --> 00:53:42,710
Prost is first. Senna, second.

740
00:53:42,960 --> 00:53:44,916
Prost jumped into the lead.

741
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:46,478
His start was better.

742
00:54:04,440 --> 00:54:07,590
LAP 45 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE

743
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:21,036
LAP 46 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE

744
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:25,911
Here is an opportunity that Senna is looking for!
And he's going through!

745
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:29,469
Oh my goodness! This is fantastic!

746
00:54:29,639 --> 00:54:32,278
Finally they clash! It goes in the favour of Prost.

747
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:38,431
If the race ends like this,
Prost wins the title.

748
00:54:39,039 --> 00:54:44,432
But, for Ayrton Senna it is a win-win situation.

749
00:54:48,360 --> 00:54:55,117
It is difficult to make people, when you are pro-Senna that

750
00:54:55,199 --> 00:54:57,713
when you say "I did not do it on purpose."

751
00:54:57,800 --> 00:55:01,076
To be honest
I don't care so much, because

752
00:55:01,960 --> 00:55:05,918
I promise you I did not do it on purpose.
But I did not open the door

753
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:09,833
which is very different,
especially in this corner.

754
00:55:09,920 --> 00:55:14,789
But if you're not racing driver
knowing the corner, knowing the track

755
00:55:14,880 --> 00:55:17,871
and knowing the chicane, you cannot judge.

756
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:22,391
It's a waste of time
to try to explain the situation.

757
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:25,552
It is my opinion. It was a race incident,

758
00:55:25,639 --> 00:55:28,552
especially when you're fighting for the championship.

759
00:55:28,639 --> 00:55:31,074
Knowing that if I wanted to open the door,

760
00:55:31,159 --> 00:55:32,990
I could not make the chicane myself.

761
00:55:33,280 --> 00:55:38,400
It was a little bit less than not yielding.
The level of aggression

762
00:55:39,639 --> 00:55:43,188
that caused the cars to collide.

763
00:55:43,639 --> 00:55:47,474
Which was, let's say, motor racing.

764
00:55:48,960 --> 00:55:52,474
But really it was what unfolded that was so wrong.

765
00:56:23,199 --> 00:56:24,552
Nannini passes.

766
00:56:24,880 --> 00:56:27,474
Nannini is now in the lead.

767
00:56:31,239 --> 00:56:32,992
Senna is still in the pits.

768
00:56:37,679 --> 00:56:41,389
Senna is back on track,
but he is far behind Nannini.

769
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:43,152
Catching up is almost impossible.

770
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:46,391
It's all or nothing,
five laps to go.

771
00:56:46,480 --> 00:56:49,949
It will be a suicidal race for Senna,
if he decides to try anything.

772
00:56:51,159 --> 00:56:53,070
Then Prost saw Ayrton return to the race

773
00:56:53,159 --> 00:56:54,148
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

774
00:56:54,239 --> 00:56:57,231
and immediately went to the stewards' office.

775
00:57:02,239 --> 00:57:04,231
Nannini, first. Senna, second.

776
00:57:04,599 --> 00:57:06,909
Senna tries to pass Nannini!

777
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:09,434
Senna is in the lead.

778
00:57:09,519 --> 00:57:10,554
LAP 51 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE.

779
00:57:11,559 --> 00:57:13,072
Waving Brazilian flags.

780
00:57:13,280 --> 00:57:15,271
All stand up!

781
00:57:15,440 --> 00:57:16,554
Ayrton Senna.

782
00:57:16,719 --> 00:57:19,074
The checkered flag!

783
00:57:19,239 --> 00:57:20,911
Senna celebrates in the cockpit.

784
00:57:21,039 --> 00:57:22,028
AYRTON SENNA WINNER - JAPANESE GRAND PRIX

785
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:27,668
He hits his helmet.
The Brazilian Ayrton Senna.

786
00:57:28,199 --> 00:57:31,590
Visibly moved,

787
00:57:32,360 --> 00:57:36,034
He raises his visor
and wipes away a tear.

788
00:57:36,280 --> 00:57:38,952
It is a fantastic victory.

789
00:57:39,239 --> 00:57:41,514
I have never seen anything like it.

790
00:57:44,480 --> 00:57:45,878
I went back to the pits,

791
00:57:45,960 --> 00:57:50,431
and I saw Ayrton,
pushed by the marshals and start again.

792
00:57:50,519 --> 00:57:54,672
Obviously I was not happy,

793
00:57:55,199 --> 00:58:00,831
and that's it I went into the garage,
I had a very strong argument with Ron

794
00:58:01,440 --> 00:58:03,112
and that's it.

795
00:58:05,880 --> 00:58:07,199
Yes No, not ...

796
00:58:07,280 --> 00:58:09,396
You have not gone before the control tower?

797
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:11,277
Garage. Or not.

798
00:58:11,360 --> 00:58:13,032
According to me you went first to the tower.

799
00:58:14,079 --> 00:58:15,398
Maybe to the tower.

800
00:58:15,480 --> 00:58:17,471
Hello, you discussed with Ron at the tower.

801
00:58:17,559 --> 00:58:22,076
The tower, yes, because Ron was already in the tower

802
00:58:22,159 --> 00:58:25,630
and we had a strong argument there. But never,

803
00:58:25,719 --> 00:58:28,836
at no situation
I was, for example, in the tower

804
00:58:28,920 --> 00:58:31,639
with Mr. Balestre alone.

805
00:58:31,719 --> 00:58:34,836
That did not happen. But I read that many many times.

806
00:58:34,920 --> 00:58:37,797
We had the argument,

807
00:58:37,880 --> 00:58:42,317
I did not even enter the race control.

808
00:58:42,639 --> 00:58:44,311
Maybe in 20 minutes.

809
00:58:44,559 --> 00:58:45,913
Fuckin' hell.

810
00:58:46,159 --> 00:58:47,478
A cup of tea?

811
00:58:48,032 --> 00:58:50,652
There was no podium celebration
immediately after the race.

812
00:58:50,739 --> 00:58:51,775
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

813
00:58:51,760 --> 00:58:56,231
Nigel, Nigel, he missed the chicane.

814
00:58:56,320 --> 00:58:58,197
He went through the slip road.

815
00:58:58,280 --> 00:59:01,670
STEWARDS OFFICE

816
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:10,552
As the wait was prolonged, the more people feared
that the decision was becoming political.

817
00:59:29,639 --> 00:59:32,355
The decision taken by the
team of FIA Commissioners

818
00:59:32,480 --> 00:59:35,630
at the Grand Prix of Japan

819
00:59:35,719 --> 00:59:38,757
is to exclude the number one car
and its driver, Ayrton Senna,

820
00:59:39,000 --> 00:59:40,876
from the final outcome of the race.

821
00:59:40,960 --> 00:59:45,958
After the race, a giant screen has
repeatedly shown the incident

822
00:59:46,039 --> 00:59:49,873
and everything that happened to
enable Senna's return to the track.

823
00:59:50,159 --> 00:59:54,119
After reviewing these images,
race officials have concluded

824
00:59:54,199 --> 00:59:58,672
that Senna failed to use the
chicane to resume racing

825
00:59:58,760 --> 01:00:02,547
Senna has infringed Article 56
of the FIA regulations.

826
01:00:03,800 --> 01:00:05,233
You are the world champion, Alain?

827
01:00:05,320 --> 01:00:06,514
Apparently, yes.

828
01:00:07,880 --> 01:00:10,713
I was not 100% sure.
I know the regulation

829
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:14,873
but you never know
how it's going to be interpreted.

830
01:00:15,039 --> 01:00:19,635
But to be very honest,
I am quite happy to leave,

831
01:00:19,760 --> 01:00:23,672
Because I think it's become absolutely impossible to work with Ayrton.

832
01:00:23,760 --> 01:00:27,594
And that's a good end for the Championship.

833
01:00:47,400 --> 01:00:48,958
What I'd like to do now

834
01:00:49,760 --> 01:00:55,516
is show you some footage
which I think is quite relevant

835
01:00:56,239 --> 01:01:00,552
because we're told you can't use escape roads to rejoin the race.

836
01:01:00,639 --> 01:01:01,708
REPLAY AUSTRIAN GRAND PRIX 1981

837
01:01:01,800 --> 01:01:06,715
Escape roads are not for escaping through.
They're in fact for stopping in,

838
01:01:06,800 --> 01:01:09,916
turning round
and going out of.

839
01:01:12,039 --> 01:01:15,271
Very important to remember
that there were no exclusions

840
01:01:15,400 --> 01:01:18,914
No penalties. No disqualifications.

841
01:01:19,559 --> 01:01:23,235
And for that, he's excluded from the Japanese Grand Prix?

842
01:01:23,320 --> 01:01:27,358
Where is the consistency? It can't be right.

843
01:01:29,280 --> 01:01:34,228
That was the first time that a team has done an appeal

844
01:01:34,320 --> 01:01:38,757
and request against its own driver.

845
01:01:39,039 --> 01:01:42,827
I was in this kind of mood where, honestly

846
01:01:43,960 --> 01:01:48,112
I wanted to be world champion,
but you know that anything was possible

847
01:01:48,199 --> 01:01:52,318
and looking at your own team going so far,

848
01:01:54,920 --> 01:01:57,114
I did not know what could happen.

849
01:01:57,480 --> 01:02:00,039
Prost was very very political.

850
01:02:01,639 --> 01:02:03,994
I think it's probably fair to say

851
01:02:04,159 --> 01:02:07,356
that he was with several teams during his career.

852
01:02:07,519 --> 01:02:10,318
and, I don't think his relationship with any of them ended happily.

853
01:02:14,280 --> 01:02:16,315
Alain, you say that you took a normal racing line

854
01:02:16,400 --> 01:02:19,119
But, I'd like to put it to you that from the aerial pictures,

855
01:02:19,199 --> 01:02:21,235
you looked as if you turned in quite early.

856
01:02:21,320 --> 01:02:24,914
It wasn't a normal line at all.

857
01:02:25,239 --> 01:02:28,072
I won 39 races
and now three championships

858
01:02:28,159 --> 01:02:32,835
Do you think I would do something like this on purpose?

859
01:02:33,719 --> 01:02:36,757
I had already turned from the corner

860
01:02:36,840 --> 01:02:40,753
maybe a little earlier, if you want,
but that was my corner.

861
01:02:42,599 --> 01:02:46,751
FIA HEADQUARTERS - PARIS
The Court of Appeals declares

862
01:02:46,920 --> 01:02:51,117
a six-month license suspension for Senna.

863
01:02:53,079 --> 01:02:57,748
A warning not only to Ayrton
Senna but for all the drivers,

864
01:02:57,840 --> 01:03:00,956
And a fine of $100,000.

865
01:03:01,039 --> 01:03:05,112
While he is one of the best drivers in the world,

866
01:03:05,199 --> 01:03:09,512
you have no right to
cause stupid accidents.

867
01:03:10,039 --> 01:03:12,918
The whole affair has been treated

868
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:18,034
is like I have total responsibility for everything that took place there

869
01:03:18,159 --> 01:03:22,994
I was blamed for everything
and I was penalized for everything.

870
01:03:23,079 --> 01:03:25,195
I was treated like a criminal.

871
01:03:26,559 --> 01:03:28,231
And this is totally unacceptable.

872
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:31,036
They took the Championship away from him

873
01:03:31,159 --> 01:03:34,994
and they suspended his license, for a period.

874
01:03:36,480 --> 01:03:42,588
To me it was the worst use of power, political power

875
01:03:43,960 --> 01:03:46,871
in my fifteen years on the Formula One circuit.

876
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:50,190
And Ayrton would never forget it.

877
01:03:50,920 --> 01:03:55,675
Alain Prost, somewhere, I know,
deep down inside, was ashamed of it.

878
01:03:56,880 --> 01:04:00,030
And the rule was actually changed later,

879
01:04:00,159 --> 01:04:04,152
to allow what Ayrton did, to become legal, because of it.

880
01:04:12,280 --> 01:04:15,994
That was quite a profound moment for Ayrton

881
01:04:16,119 --> 01:04:19,317
because Balestre had behaved
even worse than Prost.

882
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:20,474
VIVIANE SENNA

883
01:04:20,800 --> 01:04:23,757
He even thought about giving
up Formula One racing.

884
01:04:28,320 --> 01:04:30,197
I left him alone for awhile, y'know.

885
01:04:30,280 --> 01:04:31,315
VOICE OF RON DENNIS
MCLAREN TEAM MANAGER

886
01:04:31,400 --> 01:04:36,757
Then, gently persuaded him
that if you are true to your values

887
01:04:38,079 --> 01:04:43,871
if you believe that your values are, correct values,

888
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:48,311
then walking away from the dark forces

889
01:04:48,400 --> 01:04:51,835
you'll face in life
just doesn't become an option.

890
01:04:56,880 --> 01:05:02,034


891
01:05:06,280 --> 01:05:11,478
In the 1990 season he came back wiser,
the team is harmonious,

892
01:05:11,559 --> 01:05:14,233
Prost has gone out of McLaren to Ferrari

893
01:05:14,360 --> 01:05:18,717
and Senna is in a perfect position
to compete for the title.

894
01:05:20,039 --> 01:05:22,918
All drivers aspire towards their limits.

895
01:05:23,280 --> 01:05:28,148
My limit is different from that of Prost.
This is the reality.

896
01:05:28,519 --> 01:05:33,798
Instead of trying
to improve his own capacity,

897
01:05:34,119 --> 01:05:37,112
he found it easier to attack me.

898
01:05:37,480 --> 01:05:42,394
Ayrton has a small problem.
He believes that he can't kill himself,

899
01:05:42,639 --> 01:05:44,550
because he believes in God and things like this.

900
01:05:44,639 --> 01:05:47,518
I think it is very dangerous
for the other drivers.

901
01:05:47,639 --> 01:05:51,518
The fact that I believe in God,
the fact that I have faith in God,

902
01:05:52,360 --> 01:05:54,429
is not to say that I am immortal,

903
01:05:54,519 --> 01:06:02,277
It does not mean that I am immune from
danger, as has been said.

904
01:06:02,760 --> 01:06:06,434
I'm afraid of hurting me
just like everyone else,

905
01:06:06,639 --> 01:06:10,431
especially driving in Formula One,
where the threat is constant.

906
01:06:11,239 --> 01:06:13,594
SPANISH GRAND PRIX
30th SEPTEMBER 1990

907
01:06:14,400 --> 01:06:17,550
MARTIN DONNELLY
LOTUS

908
01:06:26,280 --> 01:06:27,998
Is that him?

909
01:06:28,280 --> 01:06:29,349
Who is it?

910
01:06:29,440 --> 01:06:31,748
Martin Donnelly.

911
01:06:40,320 --> 01:06:44,996
I was in the pits.
The practice was stopped.

912
01:06:46,800 --> 01:06:50,998
I hear from different people
there was an accident. It was Donnelly.

913
01:06:51,119 --> 01:06:54,668
It was bad.
It was too bad. It was a disaster.

914
01:06:54,800 --> 01:06:59,315
And I decided to go to the place
to see myself.

915
01:07:16,320 --> 01:07:20,552
A million things went through my mind.
In the end,

916
01:07:20,679 --> 01:07:24,150
I realized I was not going to give up my passion.

917
01:07:24,239 --> 01:07:28,869
Having just seen what I had seen

918
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:34,717
And I had to put myself together

919
01:07:34,840 --> 01:07:39,072
And walk up, go to the racing car and do it again

920
01:07:39,199 --> 01:07:42,351
and do it again, and do it even better than before.

921
01:07:43,039 --> 01:07:49,434
Because that was the way to kind of cover that impact it had on me.

922
01:07:50,679 --> 01:07:54,911
I was just not ready to give up.
As much as I was scared to continue

923
01:07:55,039 --> 01:07:58,873
I was not ready to give up
my aim, my target, my objective,

924
01:07:58,960 --> 01:08:03,271
my passion, my dream, my life.
This is my life.

925
01:08:43,000 --> 01:08:47,118
AYRTON SENNA 1:19.844
POLE POSITION

926
01:08:48,119 --> 01:08:53,194
As far as I hear he is out of danger, life danger

927
01:08:53,279 --> 01:08:57,353
which is a lot, considering the accident.

928
01:08:57,840 --> 01:09:00,877
And as it happened to him,
it can happen to any of us.

929
01:09:00,960 --> 01:09:02,871
There are somethings that you can calculate

930
01:09:02,960 --> 01:09:06,270
but there are things that are unexpected.

931
01:09:06,359 --> 01:09:09,351
And those unexpected things are the most dangerous ones

932
01:09:09,439 --> 01:09:11,112
like it happened to him today.

933
01:09:19,199 --> 01:09:24,114
I hope we don't see those things in the future

934
01:09:28,359 --> 01:09:33,797
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
21st OCTOBER 1990

935
01:09:34,279 --> 01:09:37,192
Amazingly,
for the third time in a row

936
01:09:37,279 --> 01:09:40,317
the championship hinged on the race in Japan.

937
01:09:42,119 --> 01:09:46,636
But this time, if Prost didn't finish, Ayrton would be champion.

938
01:09:48,279 --> 01:09:51,238
Gentlemen, good morning.

939
01:09:51,319 --> 01:09:55,359
The number of laps from green light to checkered flag will be 53 laps

940
01:09:55,439 --> 01:09:56,509
PRE-RACE MEETING FOR DRIVERS

941
01:09:57,800 --> 01:10:00,997
Dangerous behavior and / or dangerous maneuvers

942
01:10:01,119 --> 01:10:02,951
will be investigated immediately

943
01:10:03,279 --> 01:10:05,747
and may lead to the suspension of your license

944
01:10:05,840 --> 01:10:09,310
for one or more Formula One World Championship events

945
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:11,831
Any questions?

946
01:10:13,039 --> 01:10:16,112
There was a big fuck up last year with Ayrton.

947
01:10:16,199 --> 01:10:17,269
NELSON PIQUET
WORLD CHAMPION 1981, 1983, 1987

948
01:10:17,399 --> 01:10:18,798
Why have to repeat the same thing?

949
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,073
The safe thing,

950
01:10:20,159 --> 01:10:23,550
is if you take the chicane,
is the stewards stop you.

951
01:10:23,680 --> 01:10:27,309
When no traffic, let you go.

952
01:10:27,399 --> 01:10:30,789
If you have to turn around and go back toward

953
01:10:31,399 --> 01:10:35,154
against another car that's dangerous!

954
01:10:35,640 --> 01:10:36,833
Okay.

955
01:10:38,479 --> 01:10:39,673
Does everybody feel that way?

956
01:10:39,760 --> 01:10:42,149
Yes.
Yes.

957
01:10:42,239 --> 01:10:44,037
-Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

958
01:10:46,319 --> 01:10:50,198
I can't stand it. I can't stand it. This is a joke.

959
01:10:50,279 --> 01:10:53,476
After what happened last year,
it's a joke, this situation

960
01:10:53,600 --> 01:10:57,832
You just proved here, I said nothing, and you see somebody raising point.

961
01:10:57,920 --> 01:11:01,070
and you see everybody agrees.
Last year was really bad for me.

962
01:11:01,640 --> 01:11:04,154
I'm sorry. I'm sorry,
but I can not stay.

963
01:11:11,239 --> 01:11:14,788
The story down in the pit lane and on the grid is one of tension

964
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:18,634
With the world championship up for grabs,
everyone is extremely tense.

965
01:11:18,720 --> 01:11:21,951
