this had determined the
World Championship.

1037
01:15:38,840 --> 01:15:42,719
Formula One World Championship for Drivers, Ayrton Senna

1038
01:15:42,800 --> 01:15:43,835
FIA AWARDS
PARIS 1990

1039
01:15:43,920 --> 01:15:46,639
Welcome the world champion,
Ayrton Senna.

1040
01:15:53,680 --> 01:15:55,431
He knew I was right with him,

1041
01:15:55,520 --> 01:15:58,511
He moved to the inside line,
going towards the first corner.

1042
01:15:58,600 --> 01:16:01,557
I was chasing him then, and he opened a gap.

1043
01:16:02,039 --> 01:16:05,555
And knowing me, like he does know,

1044
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:10,315
he must realize that if there was a gap, I will try to overtake him.

1045
01:16:10,399 --> 01:16:14,109
Okay. Let me ask you
another difficult question.

1046
01:16:14,199 --> 01:16:16,634
If I were to count back all the world champions,

1047
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:17,788
JACKIE STEWART
FORMULA ONE WORLD CHAMPION 1969, 1971, 1973

1048
01:16:18,279 --> 01:16:22,876
the number of times they had made contact with other drivers

1049
01:16:22,960 --> 01:16:26,350
that you, in the last 36, 48 months,

1050
01:16:26,439 --> 01:16:30,069
have been in contact with more other cars and drivers

1051
01:16:30,159 --> 01:16:32,469
than they might have done in total.

1052
01:16:33,399 --> 01:16:36,631
I find amazing for you to make such a question, Stewart.

1053
01:16:36,720 --> 01:16:40,632
because you are very experienced
and you know a lot about racing.

1054
01:16:40,720 --> 01:16:44,917
And you should know
that by being a racing driver

1055
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:47,389
you are under risk, all the time.

1056
01:16:47,600 --> 01:16:51,512
By being a racing driver
means you are racing with other people.

1057
01:16:51,600 --> 01:16:54,478
And if you no longer go for a gap that exists,

1058
01:16:54,560 --> 01:16:56,198
you are no longer a racing driver.

1059
01:16:56,279 --> 01:16:59,351
Because we are competing.
We are competing to win.

1060
01:16:59,439 --> 01:17:03,911
And the main motivation to all of us,
is to compete for victory

1061
01:17:04,000 --> 01:17:06,149
It's not to come third, fourth, fifth or sixth.

1062
01:17:06,239 --> 01:17:08,230
But hasn't that always been the case?

1063
01:17:08,319 --> 01:17:11,073
But I think it's all irrelevant. All you are saying Jackie,

1064
01:17:11,159 --> 01:17:12,797
is irrelevant.

1065
01:17:12,880 --> 01:17:16,634
Because I am a driver that won more races than anybody in the past three years.

1066
01:17:16,720 --> 01:17:20,429
I'm a driver that has been on pole position more than anybody in history.

1067
01:17:20,520 --> 01:17:23,751
And I'm a driver that won two titles in the last three years.

1068
01:17:23,840 --> 01:17:26,912
I don't think ... How... I cannot comprehend how

1069
01:17:27,000 --> 01:17:30,197
how you can try to turn things around

1070
01:17:30,279 --> 01:17:32,953
To say that I've been involved in more accidents than anybody

1071
01:17:33,039 --> 01:17:34,792
Because that is not true as well!

1072
01:17:35,680 --> 01:17:37,750
The rivalry between Ayrton and Prost

1073
01:17:37,880 --> 01:17:40,154
is the biggest rivalry I've ever seen in sports

1074
01:17:40,239 --> 01:17:45,997
throughout my career. That was over 38 years
in Formula One,

1075
01:17:46,079 --> 01:17:50,278
I was involved in football,
World Championships, Olympic Games

1076
01:17:50,359 --> 01:17:52,078
and worked in many other areas,

1077
01:17:52,159 --> 01:17:55,835
but I've never seen a rivalry
similar to that between Prost and Ayrton.

1078
01:17:55,920 --> 01:18:01,198
It was a rivalry involving everything.

1079
01:18:01,319 --> 01:18:04,356
There were criticisms,
especially by Prost,

1080
01:18:04,439 --> 01:18:07,750
in relation to the behavior of Ayrton as a person.

1081
01:18:08,399 --> 01:18:12,359
But he really was a pure product of kart racing.

1082
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:17,908
He brought to Formula One
a way of racing that,

1083
01:18:18,439 --> 01:18:22,353
until that time, was particular to karts,

1084
01:18:22,479 --> 01:18:28,715
Which was a very no compromise kind of approach to racing.

1085
01:18:30,760 --> 01:18:33,717
Head to head against your rivals

1086
01:18:33,840 --> 01:18:38,993
and physical contact between the machines
was okay, was fine in karts

1087
01:18:39,079 --> 01:18:40,797
It was safe enough.

1088
01:18:42,239 --> 01:18:48,759
But to bring that into cars was something quite different.

1089
01:18:49,399 --> 01:18:54,917
And I think that was one of the things
that shocked his slightly older rivals.

1090
01:18:55,600 --> 01:18:57,318
There weren't used to that.

1091
