01:27:13,359 --> 01:27:15,715
because He is the greatest

1209
01:27:16,000 --> 01:27:18,309
and He will give me this
race after all.

1210
01:27:18,399 --> 01:27:21,038
That's what happened.

1211
01:27:21,159 --> 01:27:23,469
It is God who gave me this race
and I'm happy.

1212
01:27:23,560 --> 01:27:25,515
It was thrilling.

1213
01:28:15,560 --> 01:28:19,552
All hail the Brazilian Senna
for his victory. Congratulations.

1214
01:28:19,720 --> 01:28:22,109
I thank all of Brazil.
I thank all the fans.

1215
01:28:22,199 --> 01:28:25,795
This weekend I felt so
much warmth around me

1216
01:28:25,880 --> 01:28:28,872
that we could not do anything but win.

1217
01:28:28,960 --> 01:28:30,791
It could not have been any other way.

1218
01:28:30,960 --> 01:28:32,029
And we did.

1219
01:28:39,399 --> 01:28:43,359
SENNA FAMILY HOUSE, SAO PAULO

1220
01:29:05,720 --> 01:29:08,917
Life can be very difficult in Brazil.
You have...

1221
01:29:09,600 --> 01:29:15,197
In Brazil you have all the extremes.
You have the fantastic nature.

1222
01:29:15,279 --> 01:29:19,273
You can have all the good material things
that money can buy.

1223
01:29:19,840 --> 01:29:22,354
But at the same time,
You have lots of problems.

1224
01:29:22,439 --> 01:29:28,435
Social problems, poverty.
Some violence, as a consequence.

1225
01:29:29,239 --> 01:29:30,752
I try to help

1226
01:29:31,960 --> 01:29:34,917
a little bit, for children

1227
01:29:37,399 --> 01:29:43,953
Ayrton was so well known in Brazil

1228
01:29:44,039 --> 01:29:45,154
VIVIANE SENNA
AYRTON'S SISTER

1229
01:29:45,239 --> 01:29:47,753
there were a lot of people asking for help

1230
01:29:48,960 --> 01:29:52,872
for personal problems. Sometimes hospitals

1231
01:29:52,960 --> 01:29:56,838
and charities sought his
support and donations.

1232
01:29:58,479 --> 01:30:02,074
Ayrton gave donations and tried to work things out.

1233
01:30:03,000 --> 01:30:09,314
But did not want to make random donations.

1234
01:30:09,680 --> 01:30:14,037
He wanted to develop a whole thing,
something organized and structured

1235
01:30:14,479 --> 01:30:18,996
to help Brazil, especially the children.

1236
01:30:30,560 --> 01:30:33,996
Ayrton in '91 was in great form.

1237
01:30:34,079 --> 01:30:35,149
VOICE OF JOHN BISIGNANO
ESPN COMMENTATOR

1238
01:30:35,279 --> 01:30:37,713
I think it was his strongest year.

1239
01:30:37,800 --> 01:30:42,078
He won seven races,
Constantly on pole position.

1240
01:30:42,159 --> 01:30:44,720
His intensity was every bit as high as ever.

1241
01:30:50,279 --> 01:30:53,795
But there just seemed to be a further...wisdom.

1242
01:30:53,880 --> 01:30:55,871
Further bit of growth.

1243
01:31:00,600 --> 01:31:05,037
MEXICAN GRAND PRIX
14th JUNE 1991

1244
01:31:19,079 --> 01:31:21,435
But then the car bit him hard.

1245
01:31:22,880 --> 01:31:27,510
For the first time, he really thought
he could be hurt in a Formula One car.

1246
01:31:40,239 --> 01:31:41,832
A neurological examination

1247
01:31:41,920 --> 01:31:42,954
VOICE OF PROFESSOR SID WATKINS
F1 DOCTOR

1248
01:31:43,079 --> 01:31:45,310
detected the chest, and the
blood pressure, and the abdomen

1249
01:31:45,399 --> 01:31:46,912
and the limbs.

1250
01:31:47,000 --> 01:31:50,037
-How do you feel about this..?
-He's fine.

1251
01:31:50,119 --> 01:31:53,237
-No problems to worry about?
-No. That's all. No.

1252
01:31:55,359 --> 01:31:56,509
VOICE OF PROFESSOR SID WATKINS
F1 DOCTOR

1253
01:31:56,600 --> 01:32:00,877
It's the deepest personal relationship
I've ever had with any driver

1254
01:32:00,960 --> 01:32:05,555
Whenever I got to the circuit and ran into Senna

1255
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:09,394
he was usually being interviewed
or surrounded by people.

1256
01:32:09,479 --> 01:32:14,429
As soon as he saw me his face would always light up,
in a beautiful grin.

1257
01:32:15,119 --> 01:32:17,997
It had wonderful humility,

1258
01:32:18,119 --> 01:32:21,510
which is not common among racing drivers

1259
01:32:23,680 --> 01:32:25,796
-Okay.
-It was a pleasure.

1260
01:32:27,439 --> 01:32:28,792
Be careful.

1261
01:32:28,880 --> 01:32:30,791
You still have so much to do.

1262
01:32:30,880 --> 01:32:32,471
Yes, important.

1263
01:32:37,439 --> 01:32:39,555
Questions? Yes

1264
01:32:39,640 --> 01:32:40,675
GERMAN GRAND PRIX
28th JULY 1991

1265
01:32:40,800 --> 01:32:45,635
We talked about the chicanes
and the barriers

1266
01:32:45,720 --> 01:32:48,109
that we have there with the tyres.

1267
01:32:48,199 --> 01:32:49,792
You happen to hit those tyres

1268
01:32:49,920 --> 01:32:52,514
it is very likely the tyres throw you up in the air

1269
01:32:52,640 --> 01:32:54,914
and you end up rolling

1270
01:32:55,000 --> 01:32:56,911
That's what happened with me in Mexico

1271
01:32:57,359 --> 01:33:00,158
and that can happen here with other people.

1272
01:33:00,479 --> 01:33:03,438
I agree that for the moment

1273
01:33:03,520 --> 01:33:06,079
is not the ideal thing to have done.

1274
01:33:06,159 --> 01:33:07,354
ROLAND BRUYNSERAEDE
RACE DIRECTOR

1275
01:33:07,439 --> 01:33:11,274
The President has told yesterday
with Mr. Mosley.

1276
01:33:11,359 --> 01:33:14,670
No, no, no.
Forget Mr. Mosley.

1277
01:33:14,760 --> 01:33:16,591
And he has...

1278
01:33:16,880 --> 01:33:17,994
Forget it.

1279
01:33:18,079 --> 01:33:20,354
Okay. The president of the FISA...

1280
01:33:20,680 --> 01:33:23,716
No, forget the president.

1281
01:33:23,800 --> 01:33:27,759
We speak of the issue
raised by Mr. Senna,

1282
01:33:27,840 --> 01:33:31,878
what we do today
For the race.

1283
01:33:32,039 --> 01:33:34,234
For the race, we cannot do anything

1284
01:33:34,359 --> 01:33:37,033
I think it's better to not have those tyres there

1285
01:33:37,199 --> 01:33:41,273
I happened to lose the braking point in the first chicane yesterday

1286
01:33:41,359 --> 01:33:45,194
Let me finish. Let me finish.

1287
01:33:45,319 --> 01:33:48,630
As I went straight. It was blocked you know

1288
01:33:48,720 --> 01:33:49,835
and I couldn't turn back.

1289
01:33:49,920 --> 01:33:54,675
If we remove the tires,
we must place the cones.

1290
01:33:54,800 --> 01:33:59,157
Yeah, okay.
In that way, there is a run-off there

1291
01:33:59,239 --> 01:34:00,309
Yes

1292
01:34:01,319 --> 01:34:05,313
No, you must restart with the same point.

1293
01:34:05,399 --> 01:34:08,710
Because you must respect the distance of the race

1294
01:34:08,800 --> 01:34:10,313
We cannot come back.

1295
01:34:10,399 --> 01:34:15,554
I'm sorry,
but this regulation.

1296
01:34:15,640 --> 01:34:18,472
It is written in the regulation.
We got the letter yesterday.

1297
01:34:18,560 --> 01:34:20,390
Page three.

1298
01:34:24,239 --> 01:34:27,390
Here. The last two paragraphs.

1299
01:34:35,560 --> 01:34:38,438
Very good, penalty for her.

1300
01:34:39,239 --> 01:34:41,470
Jean-Marie, is the same thing.

1301
01:34:41,560 --> 01:34:45,234
No problem, Ayrton.
No problem.

1302
01:34:45,319 --> 01:34:48,436
Whatever is the decision, it is the right decision to make

1303
01:34:48,520 --> 01:34:49,509
You must understand.

1304
01:34:49,600 --> 01:34:51,988
The best decision is my decision.

1305
01:34:54,680 --> 01:34:57,512
I have a feeling for that.

1306
01:34:57,600 --> 01:35:00,751
No, because you don't know my decision.

1307
01:35:00,880 --> 01:35:03,952
It's the best, everytime, my decision.

1308
01:35:04,079 --> 01:35:05,512
And my decision is

1309
01:35:05,600 --> 01:35:09,832
Democratic vote. Only the drivers.

1310
01:35:09,920 --> 01:35:12,194
By hand.

1311
01:35:17,079 --> 01:35:23,952
Who are in favor we replace the
tyre by the cones?

1312
01:35:25,199 --> 01:35:26,269
Raise your hand.

1313
01:35:27,439 --> 01:35:29,828
Stop.

1314
01:35:29,960 --> 01:35:32,189
Against?

1315
01:35:32,279 --> 01:35:36,193
Abstain? Everybody agree, okay.

1316
01:35:36,279 --> 01:35:40,796
Immediately, the wall will replace the tyre by the cone, okay.

1317
01:35:41,680 --> 01:35:44,671
3 HOURS LATER

1318
01:35:49,960 --> 01:35:52,997
Alain, what happened going into that chicane?

1319
01:35:53,079 --> 01:35:56,550
I tried to overtake Senna. It was ...

1320
01:35:57,239 --> 01:36:01,073
Blocked me during the whole race, not very correct.

1321
01:36:02,760 --> 01:36:04,556
I think everyone knows Prost by now.

1322
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:07,996
He always complain either by the car, or the tyres,

1323
01:36:08,079 --> 01:36:12,948
the team, or the mechanics, or the fuel,
or the other drivers or the circuit.

1324
01:36:13,039 --> 01:36:15,600
There's always somebody else blame, it's never his fault.

1325
01:36:15,680 --> 01:36:16,748
Yes, no problem.

1326
01:36:16,840 --> 01:36:20,673
So I have nothing to lose.
I can't win the championship,

1327
01:36:20,760 --> 01:36:26,356
but if I find him again, the same way,
I push him out.

1328
01:36:29,079 --> 01:36:32,310
Prost was sacked from Ferrari
because he had criticized the car.

1329
01:36:32,399 --> 01:36:34,152
VOICE OF RICHARD WILLIAMS
SPORTS JOURNALIST, THE GUARDIAN

1330
01:36:34,239 --> 01:36:37,231
The only thing he could do, really, was take a year off

1331
01:36:37,319 --> 01:36:39,470
telling everybody he was on a sabbatical.

1332
01:36:43,159 --> 01:36:47,551
My favorite part of a Grand Prix
was the starting grid

1333
01:36:48,680 --> 01:36:53,707
and used to do the pit walk
and walk down the center of the grid

1334
01:36:53,800 --> 01:36:57,679
and give an update on every team that was on the grid.

1335
01:36:58,720 --> 01:37:00,471
Now, I don't know if it was because

1336
01:37:00,560 --> 01:37:03,518
I was getting closer to the front of the grid

1337
01:37:03,600 --> 01:37:06,159
or close to the start of the race

1338
01:37:06,239 --> 01:37:09,231
but I swear to you, as a fact,

1339
01:37:09,920 --> 01:37:13,707
when I stood next to Ayrton Senna's car

1340
01:37:13,800 --> 01:37:18,157
at certain times, the hair would stand up...on my arms.

1341
01:37:19,239 --> 01:37:23,153
There was an energy, there was a force,

1342
01:37:23,239 --> 01:37:25,515
There was a spirit in that cockpit

1343
01:37:25,600 --> 01:37:31,435
that you could not find
around any other car on that grid.

1344
01:37:32,399 --> 01:37:34,755
It was absolutely electrifying.

1345
01:37:37,720 --> 01:37:40,996
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
19th OCTOBER 1991

1346
01:37:53,520 --> 01:37:56,636
If I finish second place,
The championship will be over.

1347
01:37:56,720 --> 01:37:58,914
If Mansell does not win,

1348
01:37:59,000 --> 01:38:02,355
then, it's almost certain that
the championship will be over as well.

1349
01:38:22,159 --> 01:38:24,354
LAP 9 OF 53

1350
01:38:24,800 --> 01:38:28,155
Mansell tries to overtake, but he goes straight on.

1351
01:38:28,239 --> 01:38:30,833
Mansell goes straight on!

1352
01:38:31,000 --> 01:38:34,515
The Championship is over.
Mansell cannot get out of the gravel trap.

1353
01:38:34,600 --> 01:38:35,715
AYRTON SENNA
THREE-TIME WORLD CHAMPION

1354
01:38:35,800 --> 01:38:41,431
Ayrton Senna of Brazil,
three-time Formula One World Champion!

1355
01:38:41,880 --> 01:38:46,350
A lifetime dedicated to this moment

1356
01:38:47,520 --> 01:38:50,956
by a genius of international sport.

1357
01:38:51,039 --> 01:38:54,077
Three-time world champion
and many other titles ahead of him.

1358
01:38:54,239 --> 01:38:56,195
And only 31 years of age.

1359
01:38:56,279 --> 01:38:59,954
33 wins, three world titles.

1360
01:39:00,039 --> 01:39:04,908
Breaking record after record.
He celebrates as only Senna can do.

1361
01:39:05,039 --> 01:39:10,511
The third world title puts Senna
among the greatest of all time.

1362
01:39:33,560 --> 01:39:35,436
It is very special for me.

1363
01:39:35,560 --> 01:39:37,038
Thank you so much.

1364
01:39:37,680 --> 01:39:41,389
SAO PAULO
5th NOVEMBER 1991

1365
01:39:42,039 --> 01:39:47,478
I followed Senna, walked with him

1366
01:39:48,600 --> 01:39:52,274
on the streets of many countries around the world,

1367
01:39:52,359 --> 01:39:57,194
especially to get to the circuits,
such as in Japan,

1368
01:39:57,319 --> 01:40:01,949
where there is a one kilometer walk to reach the hotel

1369
01:40:02,079 --> 01:40:05,675
and to reach the circuit you
must cross an amusement park

1370
01:40:05,840 --> 01:40:12,029
And I thought: "How can a person
be worshipped in this way?"

1371
01:40:13,520 --> 01:40:16,158
It was a worship without limits.

1372
01:40:33,680 --> 01:40:36,716
I kissed the hands of Senna, the left hand
of Senna, three-times world champion.

1373
01:40:36,880 --> 01:40:41,270
I want to Senna.
I want to hug him and kiss him.

1374
01:40:41,359 --> 01:40:43,350
I have got a box with
photos and newspaper articles.

1375
01:40:43,479 --> 01:40:45,037
Everything you can imagine.

1376
01:40:45,159 --> 01:40:47,548
He is the only good thing in Brazil, right?

1377
01:40:49,560 --> 01:40:53,269
After that third world championship
I saw another Senna.

1378
01:40:53,399 --> 01:40:58,952
He was very satisfied, very confident.
He knew the sport better than ever.

1379
01:40:59,039 --> 01:41:02,873
He had saw with real eyes
for the good and the bad

1380
01:41:03,000 --> 01:41:06,230
and he still loved it, as much as anyone in the paddock.

1381
01:41:12,239 --> 01:41:14,707
It is a wonderful party.

1382
01:41:14,880 --> 01:41:17,917
Anything goes. What matters is happiness.

1383
01:41:18,039 --> 01:41:20,155
Have you spoken about Formula One today?

1384
01:41:20,239 --> 01:41:23,755
Formula One is too rigid.
Today is Carnival.

1385
01:41:30,359 --> 01:41:34,432
Have any of your girls
ever told you: "Faster, Ayrton?

1386
01:41:39,600 --> 01:41:41,078
Yes

1387
01:41:43,359 --> 01:41:45,350
Ayrton acheiving the third world title

1388
01:41:45,439 --> 01:41:48,829
was the culmination of a script
he had written for himself

1389
01:41:48,920 --> 01:41:50,671
well before entering Formula One,

1390
01:41:50,760 --> 01:41:54,115
because he knew he could do it
and could do even more.

1391
01:41:54,920 --> 01:41:58,229
The great idol of sport in Brazil.

1392
01:41:59,079 --> 01:42:02,755
With the third title, he became
the world's great sporting idol.

1393
01:42:10,279 --> 01:42:13,908
There is a great desire in me on improving.

1394
01:42:14,760 --> 01:42:17,752
Getting better. Better makes me happy.

1395
01:42:17,840 --> 01:42:22,470
In retirement I feel I am slowing down my learning process

1396
01:42:22,560 --> 01:42:26,234
my learning curve is getting flatter, whatever

1397
01:42:26,319 --> 01:42:28,880
Then, it doesn't make me very happy.

1398
01:42:30,319 --> 01:42:35,519
And that applies not only as a professional,
as a racing driver but as a man.

1399
01:42:36,800 --> 01:42:38,153
Of course,

1400
01:42:39,960 --> 01:42:44,192
I shall have a lot more to learn as a man
than as a racing driver,

1401
01:42:44,279 --> 01:42:47,511
because my career could last not many years

1402
01:42:48,199 --> 01:42:51,475
My life, hopefully, would still go for a long time.

1403
01:42:52,600 --> 01:42:57,070
Maybe I'm only at the half of my life right now, so...

1404
01:42:59,159 --> 01:43:03,756
There is a lot to go, a lot to learn, a lot to do still, in life.

1405
01:43:04,920 --> 01:43:09,435
And happiness will come when I feel complete, as a whole.

1406
01:43:10,159 --> 01:43:12,878
which definitely I don't feel today.

1407
01:43:12,960 --> 01:43:16,110
But I have plenty of time to fulfil that too.

1408
01:43:19,600 --> 01:43:23,309


1409
01:43:28,279 --> 01:43:32,319
For the next season, the level
of competition was distorted

1410
01:43:32,399 --> 01:43:36,029
by what was going on, technically,
with Williams' car.

1411
01:43:38,479 --> 01:43:43,189
The car balanced itself.
Each corner was controlled by computer.

1412
01:43:45,760 --> 01:43:49,992
All the driver had to do was put his right
foot down and go as fast as possible.

1413
01:43:50,079 --> 01:43:53,708
So in a car without that you were
at a serious disadvantage.

1414
01:43:54,279 --> 01:43:57,750
McLaren still well off
the Williams-Renault pace.

1415
01:43:57,880 --> 01:44:01,509
with that result the three times
world champion Ayrton Senna

1416
01:44:01,600 --> 01:44:04,319
has no chance of retaining his title.

1417
01:44:06,079 --> 01:44:09,072
When you go into this sort

1418
01:44:11,760 --> 01:44:13,273
electronic war

1419
01:44:16,439 --> 01:44:20,911
you can find yourself completely stuck.

1420
01:44:21,800 --> 01:44:26,475
The eletronics do a given situation.

1421
01:44:27,079 --> 01:44:29,229
And no matter who you put in the car,

1422
01:44:29,319 --> 01:44:30,354
NIGEL MANSELL WORLD CHAMPION 1992

1423
01:44:30,439 --> 01:44:32,192
the eletronics will do the work and not the driver.

1424
01:44:33,319 --> 01:44:36,153
I do not think that is really what you want

1425
01:44:36,279 --> 01:44:39,828
to have a truly World Championship

1426
01:44:41,960 --> 01:44:42,994
of drivers.

1427
01:44:43,119 --> 01:44:44,552
The negotiations were lengthy

1428
01:44:44,640 --> 01:44:47,438
and we still do not know who will be
Prost's teammate.

1429
01:44:47,680 --> 01:44:50,034
The three-time world champion has signed

1430
01:44:50,119 --> 01:44:51,917
a two-year contract with Williams

1431
01:44:52,000 --> 01:44:54,194
and during the week
will begin testing the car.

1432
01:44:56,640 --> 01:44:58,710
The only thing I asked in the contract was that

1433
01:44:58,800 --> 01:45:01,074
I did not want to be a teammate with Ayrton.

1434
01:45:01,159 --> 01:45:02,229
VOICE OF ALAIN PROST

1435
01:45:02,319 --> 01:45:03,832
It has to be clear.

1436
01:45:03,920 --> 01:45:06,194
And they have accepted that, very quickly

1437
01:45:06,319 --> 01:45:08,037
saying no, it was not our intention.

1438
01:45:08,119 --> 01:45:10,554
This was the only thing I asked in the contract

1439
01:45:10,640 --> 01:45:12,231
because I wanted to be world champion

1440
01:45:12,319 --> 01:45:14,595
and do not want to lose the opportunity.

1441
01:45:15,479 --> 01:45:20,030
I that when I drove the car in
September, in Estoril

1442
01:45:20,119 --> 01:45:22,997
and the first few laps, it was wet

1443
01:45:23,079 --> 01:45:25,229
and the car was absolutely unbelievable.

1444
01:45:25,319 --> 01:45:29,154
I have never driven a car like this in my whole career.

1445
01:45:29,279 --> 01:45:32,158
But, yeah.

1446
01:45:32,600 --> 01:45:36,434
that car at that time was a good second, minimum a good second quicker.

1447
01:45:37,119 --> 01:45:39,395
It is no secret that I'd been

1448
01:45:40,159 --> 01:45:42,957
trying very hard to get some...

1449
01:45:45,760 --> 01:45:47,796
some deal with Williams.

1450
01:45:49,079 --> 01:45:51,115
The situation is very complex.

1451
01:45:52,439 --> 01:45:53,667
It is...

1452
01:45:56,279 --> 01:45:58,953
It's not nice, it's not clear either.

1453
01:46:04,560 --> 01:46:07,154
I'm pretty sure of one thing:

1454
01:46:08,000 --> 01:46:12,152
I'm the one that has more to lose

1455
01:46:12,279 --> 01:46:19,238
Because I'm at an age near the peak of my career

1456
01:46:19,319 --> 01:46:24,234
and the number of years in the career
of a Formula One driver is limited.

1457
01:46:27,119 --> 01:46:31,829
So if I stop,
I'd lose out more than anyone else,

1458
01:46:31,960 --> 01:46:35,270
at both professionally and personally.

1459
01:46:36,960 --> 01:46:40,998
ADRIANE GALISTEU

1460
01:46:42,119 --> 01:46:46,988


1461
01:46:51,239 --> 01:46:55,596
In 1993, Ayrton drove
his car so brilliantly.

1462
01:46:55,760 --> 01:46:57,591
For me, it was his best season.

1463
01:46:57,720 --> 01:46:59,711
BRAZILIAN GRAND PRIX

1464
01:47:00,159 --> 01:47:01,194
EUROPEAN GRAND PRIX

1465
01:47:01,279 --> 01:47:04,113
He did accomplish,
some of his greatest drives.

1466
01:47:04,199 --> 01:47:05,269
MONACO GRAND PRIX

1467
01:47:05,359 --> 01:47:09,194
even though he spent most of his time
looking at the back of that Williams,

1468
01:47:09,279 --> 01:47:11,110
which was much faster than his.

1469
01:47:13,039 --> 01:47:14,757
French racing driver Alain Prost

1470
01:47:14,840 --> 01:47:18,389
has won the Formula One World Drivers Championship
for the fourth time ...

1471
01:47:18,479 --> 01:47:21,789
Prost won the championship and duly retired,

1472
01:47:21,880 --> 01:47:23,791
Thus getting out of the way.

1473
01:47:25,479 --> 01:47:29,234
It seems like a little goodbye from you to McLaren.

1474
01:47:29,319 --> 01:47:32,630
Do you think it
was the last season for McLaren?

1475
01:47:32,720 --> 01:47:35,154
I think so. I think it will be my last season.

1476
01:47:35,520 --> 01:47:37,396
Now, I have a three-year contract

1477
01:47:37,479 --> 01:47:41,757
And then I had a moment in July

1478
01:47:41,840 --> 01:47:45,832
I have a phonecall from Frank and said:

1479
01:47:45,920 --> 01:47:50,277
"I need to talk to you.
I have a big pressure from Renault

1480
01:47:50,880 --> 01:47:54,634
"And I need to talk to you about something."

1481
01:47:54,720 --> 01:47:59,713
I said, 'Okay, Frank.
I think I know what you want to talk about.

1482
01:48:00,680 --> 01:48:06,436
"But I'm on holiday."
And four or five days holiday.

1483
01:48:06,520 --> 01:48:09,238
"If the Renault people
want to talk to me,

1484
01:48:09,319 --> 01:48:11,275
"They come see me."

1485
01:48:11,359 --> 01:48:15,353
And in fact he come himself, with his plan

1486
01:48:15,439 --> 01:48:18,636
came to see me and trying to explain to me that

1487
01:48:21,880 --> 01:48:26,237
Renault they are thinking of having Ayrton in the team with me there,

1488
01:48:26,359 --> 01:48:27,952
after.

1489
01:48:29,039 --> 01:48:34,273
I said, 'Okay. That is not fair. We have a contract.

1490
01:48:34,399 --> 01:48:38,677
"Just thinking of that is not fair, in the middle of the season.

1491
01:48:38,760 --> 01:48:42,036
"Let's be fair. Lets wait a little bit"

1492
01:48:42,840 --> 01:48:46,548
"A few races,
and we'll see what happens. "

1493
01:48:47,399 --> 01:48:50,118
And in fact I'm going to tell you something that

1494
01:48:50,199 --> 01:48:53,158
nobody knows,
or very few people know,

1495
01:48:53,239 --> 01:48:56,676
but it is good to talk about this.

1496
01:48:56,800 --> 01:49:00,838
I did not want to be a teammate with
Ayrton's again.

1497
01:49:01,880 --> 01:49:07,671
I did not want to
continue with the perception of people saying:

1498
01:49:07,760 --> 01:49:11,877
"Ayrton is the poor guy with the small car,

1499
01:49:12,680 --> 01:49:17,878
"When Alain he wins it's normal,
because he has the best car. "

1500
01:49:18,600 --> 01:49:21,671
Then I said:
"Well, you want Ayrton and I understand very well.

1501
01:49:21,760 --> 01:49:26,310
"But you pay me for the contract for the next year, and I stop."

1502
01:49:26,399 --> 01:49:27,912
I did not want to stop.

1503
01:49:28,000 --> 01:49:33,596
I really did not want to stop.
But to see a situation going again,

1504
01:49:34,079 --> 01:49:36,912
especially in your own country,

1505
01:49:38,520 --> 01:49:41,033
going in this direction again,

1506
01:49:41,119 --> 01:49:44,873
I took my decision myself, very quickly.

1507
01:49:44,960 --> 01:49:48,077
But I wanted to tell them just one month or two month later

1508
01:49:48,159 --> 01:49:49,717
Because I wanted to be world champion.

1509
01:49:49,800 --> 01:49:51,233
I did not want to lose the opportunity.

1510
01:49:51,319 --> 01:49:54,038
When I saw that I was going to be world champion,

1511
01:49:54,119 --> 01:49:57,873
I said, "Okay. You pay the contract and I stop.
I've had enough. Okay? "

1512
01:49:57,960 --> 01:49:59,791
That's what I had done. I did not want to stop.

1513
01:49:59,880 --> 01:50:02,269
I stopped Formula One, only because of that.

1514
01:50:02,359 --> 01:50:04,668
Otherwise I wanted to continue.

1515
01:50:04,920 --> 01:50:08,628
Ayrton fought so hard to win at
Monaco, but did not make it,

1516
01:50:08,760 --> 01:50:14,118
fought to win at Suzuka, but did not make it,

1517
01:50:14,199 --> 01:50:18,193
and when he was struggling to get into Williams

1518
01:50:18,279 --> 01:50:21,590
he thought it was the end of his career.

1519
01:50:21,800 --> 01:50:25,997
Sometimes it makes no sense ... We always say

1520
01:50:26,079 --> 01:50:30,676
that we must fight for our ideals,
for what we want out of life.

1521
01:50:30,760 --> 01:50:35,708
But sometimes the battles
do not bring the desired results.

1522
01:50:37,720 --> 01:50:42,998
AUSTRALIAN GRAND PRIX
FINAL RACE OF 1993

1523
01:50:44,479 --> 01:50:48,029
We try to do the best we can

1524
01:50:48,199 --> 01:50:49,599
Of course.

1525
01:50:49,680 --> 01:50:53,797
We put behind us, what had happened.

1526
01:50:55,119 --> 01:50:56,394
Sure.

1527
01:50:56,479 --> 01:50:57,673
Good.

1528
01:50:58,119 --> 01:51:02,796
Even without you saying anything, that was my goal.

1529
01:51:02,960 --> 01:51:04,154
Yeah, okay.

1530
01:51:04,319 --> 01:51:06,197
Even if we didn't talk at all

1531
01:51:06,279 --> 01:51:11,194
I wouldn't change ... I do exactly as I've always tried.

1532
01:51:19,960 --> 01:51:21,029
VOICE OF MARK FOGARTY
F1 JOURNALIST

1533
01:51:21,119 --> 01:51:23,475
Ayrton, what did Ron Dennis say to you
when you first stepped down from the car?

1534
01:51:23,880 --> 01:51:26,757
It's never too late to change your mind.

1535
01:51:29,479 --> 01:51:32,949
But anyway he said he was happy for me and...

1536
01:51:33,079 --> 01:51:36,230
It's funny. That's what he told me as well.

1537
01:51:36,359 --> 01:51:37,679
That's Ron.

1538
01:51:40,600 --> 01:51:44,387
And I said you know, we must keep the good times, the good moments,

1539
01:51:44,479 --> 01:51:47,916
and lets finish that way. Finish with the good things.

1540
01:51:56,680 --> 01:52:00,957
It was Senna's last race
for McLaren

1541
01:52:01,960 --> 01:52:04,314
Prost's last race with Williams.

1542
01:52:04,800 --> 01:52:07,712
And although nobody knew at that time,

1543
01:52:07,800 --> 01:52:12,112
it was the last time
either of them were on the podium.

1544
01:52:13,399 --> 01:52:19,555
AYRTON SENNA
WINNER AUSTRALIAN GRAND PRIX

1545
01:52:39,239 --> 01:52:43,028
But from this moment, where I am on the podium,

1546
01:52:43,119 --> 01:52:45,475
close to him, on the same level,

1547
01:52:45,920 --> 01:52:49,275
he has changed completely.

1548
01:52:49,880 --> 01:52:52,997
He was really another person,

1549
01:52:53,079 --> 01:52:56,755
You have before this podium, and then you have after this podium.

1550
01:52:56,880 --> 01:52:59,074
It was absolutely unbelievable.

1551
01:52:59,159 --> 01:53:01,548
It was a different person,

1552
01:53:02,319 --> 01:53:04,675
different driver, in my opinion,

1553
01:53:04,760 --> 01:53:07,149
and different personality.

1554
01:53:07,239 --> 01:53:10,152
He just behaved completely different.

1555
01:53:10,239 --> 01:53:12,548
At the press conference,

1556
01:53:14,640 --> 01:53:18,349
It was lucky that we had all the TVs waiting for us

1557
01:53:18,439 --> 01:53:24,037
but he was talking and speaking, asking question to me all the time

1558
01:53:24,119 --> 01:53:28,318
talking as he had never talked before.

1559
01:53:28,680 --> 01:53:32,559
It was certainly right to go to McLaren after Lotus.

1560
01:53:32,640 --> 01:53:34,551
That was absolutely the right choice.

1561
01:53:36,199 --> 01:53:40,556
And to pit himself against Alain Prost

1562
01:53:42,640 --> 01:53:46,394
was a
very brave and very shrewd thing to do.

1563
01:53:46,520 --> 01:53:49,636
Shrewd because he knew, or he believed,

1564
01:53:49,720 --> 01:53:51,198
that he was better than Prost

1565
01:53:51,279 --> 01:53:54,396
and, by measuring himself against the man who was,

1566
01:53:54,479 --> 01:53:58,074
accepted as the yardstick of
Formula One at the time,

1567
01:53:58,159 --> 01:54:04,155
he  could prove
for good and all, his own qualities.

1568
01:54:04,760 --> 01:54:06,989
So, he could see that there was

1569
01:54:07,079 --> 01:54:11,073
another team that had a better car
than McLaren,

1570
01:54:11,159 --> 01:54:14,277
and the best car by a mile in the early '90s.

1571
01:54:14,359 --> 01:54:18,194
In '92 they walked the
World Championship with Nigel Mansell

1572
01:54:18,279 --> 01:54:20,668
and in '93 they walked it with Prost.

1573
01:54:21,680 --> 01:54:24,796
So he wanted to be in that car in '94.

1574
01:54:25,600 --> 01:54:29,354
And that was where his instinct let him down.

1575
01:54:30,079 --> 01:54:35,313
Probably, given the known factors, given the parameters,

1576
01:54:35,399 --> 01:54:37,152
it was the right decision.

1577
01:54:37,239 --> 01:54:41,233
And you would go back and look at the conditions

1578
01:54:41,319 --> 01:54:44,676
and you make exactly the right decision.

1579
01:54:44,760 --> 01:54:48,036
Exactly that decision.
It happened to be the wrong one.

1580
01:54:48,960 --> 01:54:51,554
But there was no way he could have known that,

1581
01:54:51,680 --> 01:54:56,878
until he actually stepped into the Williams car for the first time in '94.

1582
01:54:57,920 --> 01:55:00,797
Ladies and Gentlemen,
Brazilian driver Ayrton Senna.

1583
01:55:00,880 --> 01:55:02,073
ANNOUNCEMENT OF WILLIAMS DRIVERS

1584
01:55:06,079 --> 01:55:11,996
Ayrton is arguably the best driver available,
the best driver currently racing.

1585
01:55:12,520 --> 01:55:13,747
FRANK WILLIAMS

1586
01:55:13,840 --> 01:55:14,795
The team is geared to being successful.

1587
01:55:14,880 --> 01:55:20,238
All our partners,
investors and sponsors expect that of us.

1588
01:55:20,359 --> 01:55:24,319
Ayrton is therefore, the best piece of equipment, if you like,

1589
01:55:24,399 --> 01:55:28,551
that we can put into the machine
to deliver, to our requirements.

1590
01:55:28,640 --> 01:55:30,789
The lnternational Motorsports Federation

1591
01:55:30,880 --> 01:55:33,952
has banned some of the controversial computer devices

1592
01:55:34,039 --> 01:55:37,032
which help drivers in Formula One motor racing.

1593
01:55:37,119 --> 01:55:39,634
The ban is designed to stop the domination of the richest Formula One teams like

1594
01:55:39,720 --> 01:55:40,708


1595
01:55:40,800 --> 01:55:43,552
Williams-Renault, the World Champions.

1596
01:55:46,560 --> 01:55:48,436
For Ayrton Senna, it is
a race against time.

1597
01:55:48,600 --> 01:55:51,557
He has to attune himself to be an integral
part of the team and adapt to the new car.

1598
01:55:51,640 --> 01:55:54,518
He says he is not yet comfortable.

1599
01:55:54,600 --> 01:55:59,275
The car no longer has the electronic
components used last year.

1600
01:55:59,439 --> 01:56:03,913
He is without traction control, special
brakes and active suspension.

1601
01:56:04,039 --> 01:56:09,716
The cars are much less stable

1602
01:56:09,800 --> 01:56:13,872
without the electronically controlled suspension.

1603
01:56:13,960 --> 01:56:17,918
As a result, they are more difficult to drive

1604
01:56:18,319 --> 01:56:23,394
and it is very likely that more cars will leave the track.

1605
01:56:24,119 --> 01:56:28,716
So we might see more cars crashing,
giving more excitement to the audience.

1606
01:56:28,960 --> 01:56:31,554
Also for us, as long as nothing happens to the drivers.

1607
01:56:31,640 --> 01:56:35,234
Otherwise, it is not a good situation.

1608
01:56:35,960 --> 01:56:37,871
Senna in second place.

1609
01:56:37,960 --> 01:56:39,712
BRAZILIAN GRAND PRIX
27th MARCH 1994

1610
01:56:39,800 --> 01:56:42,314
Almost 8 seconds between them now.

1611
01:56:43,279 --> 01:56:46,636
LAP 56 OF 71

1612
01:57:00,720 --> 01:57:03,631
We are certainly not happy with the way,

1613
01:57:03,760 --> 01:57:04,795
PATRICK HEAD
CHIEF ENGINEER WILLIAMS

1614
01:57:04,920 --> 01:57:08,390
things are with the car, right as they are at this moment.

1615
01:57:08,479 --> 01:57:10,630
The handling isn't particularly good.

1616
01:57:11,399 --> 01:57:14,436
PACIFIC GRAND PRIX
17th APRIL 1994

1617
01:57:16,000 --> 01:57:18,912
The cars weren't supposed to have any of the electronic aids

1618
01:57:19,000 --> 01:57:21,309
that they had the previous year.

1619
01:57:21,399 --> 01:57:22,992
But Senna became convinced

1620
01:57:23,079 --> 01:57:26,197
that the Benetton being
driven by Michael Schumacher

1621
01:57:26,279 --> 01:57:27,269
MICHAEL SCHUMACHER
BENNETTON FORD - WINNER

1622
01:57:27,359 --> 01:57:30,033
who had won the first two races of the season,
had retained some of those,

1623
01:57:30,119 --> 01:57:31,154
FLAVIO BRIATORE
BENETTON TEAM MANAGER

1624
01:57:31,279 --> 01:57:35,671
particularly, the traction control,
the thing that eliminates the wheelspin.

1625
01:57:39,159 --> 01:57:43,676
It didn't stack up that he was being blown away by the Benetton.

1626
01:57:44,520 --> 01:57:45,475
He wanted us to protest,

1627
01:57:45,560 --> 01:57:46,675
VOICE OF FRANK WILLIAMS
TEAM MANAGER WILLIAMS

1628
01:57:47,520 --> 01:57:48,838
but we didn't do it.

1629
01:57:53,520 --> 01:57:58,877
SAN MARINO GRAND PRIX, IMOLA
APRIL 1994

1630
01:58:09,680 --> 01:58:14,230
If he carried with him any emotion, going into that race,

1631
01:58:15,239 --> 01:58:18,835
that was different from previous races,

1632
01:58:18,920 --> 01:58:22,673
it would probably had been the frustration

1633
01:58:22,760 --> 01:58:28,038
of knowing that his principal rival
was driving a car

1634
01:58:28,159 --> 01:58:31,675
with an illegal system on it.

1635
01:58:33,880 --> 01:58:39,398
That would always incense his sense of fair play.

1636
01:58:41,319 --> 01:58:44,436
I would put anything that was

1637
01:58:44,520 --> 01:58:46,670
abnormal about his behavior,

1638
01:58:46,760 --> 01:58:48,671
down to that knowledge and belief.

1639
01:58:50,079 --> 01:58:53,868
I must say that what he said,
because I cannot judge myself.

1640
01:58:53,960 --> 01:58:58,238
but was convinced the
Benetton was cheating.

1641
01:58:58,760 --> 01:59:04,630
He was very upset and he
was in big trouble because of that

1642
01:59:05,159 --> 01:59:11,076
Again, not very happy with the car...The performance of the car

1643
01:59:11,520 --> 01:59:16,149
So he was obviously not very happy,

1644
01:59:18,079 --> 01:59:20,310
saying that he could not find the motivation

1645
01:59:20,439 --> 01:59:25,069
Many times he told me:
"I can not be motivated against Michael,

1646
01:59:25,159 --> 01:59:26,877
"Against other drivers."

1647
01:59:26,960 --> 01:59:30,190
It really like

1648
01:59:32,239 --> 01:59:35,710
if he had lost his passion,

1649
01:59:35,800 --> 01:59:39,712
he had problems with the car,
problems with the team, safety.

1650
01:59:39,800 --> 01:59:42,359
maybe some small personal problems, possible.

1651
01:59:42,680 --> 01:59:46,992
But he had lost his skilling.

1652
01:59:47,640 --> 01:59:49,994
And that was very surprising.

1653
01:59:50,600 --> 01:59:57,311
It was very apparent to me,
and to several other people aro und Ayrton.

1654
01:59:59,520 --> 02:00:03,559
Josef, his trainer
and probably one of his closest friends,

1655
02:00:03,640 --> 02:00:07,189
Sid Watkins, all three of us

1656
02:00:08,000 --> 02:00:11,878
for different reasons,
very quickly formed the opinion

1657
02:00:11,960 --> 02:00:15,872
that Ayrton quickly regretted leaving the team.

1658
02:00:17,760 --> 02:00:24,551
Not specifically because of competitiveness or uncompetitiveness,

1659
02:00:24,760 --> 02:00:31,597
but more because he didn't expect
to find himself in such a different culture,

1660
02:00:31,920 --> 02:00:38,154
and one which was quite alien to the way he was.

1661
02:00:54,840 --> 02:00:59,152
We are here starting from zero.
So basically, the championship starts here.

1662
02:00:59,239 --> 02:01:03,711
It's not a comfortable position to be in,
but that's the reality.

1663
02:01:03,800 --> 02:01:08,715
You've won here three times already.
You really do need to make it four.

1664
02:01:08,800 --> 02:01:10,471
I would love to.

1665
02:01:10,880 --> 02:01:15,158
FRIDAY
29th APRIL 1994

1666
02:01:50,880 --> 02:01:54,350
Senna was so nervous that weekend.
I had never seen him so tense.

1667
02:01:54,439 --> 02:01:55,838
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

1668
02:02:00,560 --> 02:02:04,074
I never saw him smile
even for a moment.

1669
02:02:05,520 --> 02:02:11,358
He maintained a bemused, bored, even a sad demeanour.

1670
02:02:18,159 --> 02:02:20,150
It is the balance.

1671
02:02:20,239 --> 02:02:22,230
It is unstable.

1672
02:02:27,840 --> 02:02:30,069
The car has worsened.

1673
02:02:32,880 --> 02:02:35,474
Is it generally one more balanced than the other?

1674
02:02:35,560 --> 02:02:37,073
or is it constantly changing?

1675
02:02:37,399 --> 02:02:39,515
There's abit more understeer.

1676
02:02:39,600 --> 02:02:43,990
In the first round, tended to understeer.

1677
02:02:44,600 --> 02:02:48,479
Then, in the second, has changed abruptly.

1678
02:02:50,399 --> 02:02:52,435
Oversteer and understeer?

1679
02:02:52,560 --> 02:02:53,595
Yes

1680
02:02:54,600 --> 02:02:56,511
Instead of mid-corner,

1681
02:02:56,600 --> 02:02:58,829
it breakaways at the entrance

1682
02:02:59,840 --> 02:03:02,592
When it's supposed to breakaway, it breaks more.

1683
02:03:10,039 --> 02:03:16,912
He was getting into a car, that was like kind of a unbroken code if you like.

1684
02:03:18,520 --> 02:03:21,716
It had a lot of problems, a lot of vices.

1685
02:03:22,479 --> 02:03:25,631
that needed to be worked on and ironed out.

1686
02:03:25,720 --> 02:03:28,917
some of them seemed pretty fundamental.

1687
02:03:29,000 --> 02:03:33,038
One of the thing that a driver hates, above all else

1688
02:03:33,119 --> 02:03:36,795
is a car that changes its behavior in the middle of a corner.

1689
02:03:37,159 --> 02:03:39,798
There are two things,
oversteer and understeer.

1690
02:03:39,920 --> 02:03:42,387
Oversteer is what we used to call the four-wheel drift, y'know.

1691
02:03:42,479 --> 02:03:45,789
When you steer the car with the throttle and then

1692
02:03:46,720 --> 02:03:49,677
and you turn the steering wheel to balance it.

1693
02:03:49,760 --> 02:03:52,149
in such a way that you appear to be going in the opposite direction

1694
02:03:52,239 --> 02:03:54,310
from where you want to go, but actually the car drifts

1695
02:03:54,399 --> 02:03:56,230
slides around the corner.

1696
02:03:56,399 --> 02:03:59,948
Understeer is when
you have to put more steer in on than you expect.

1697
02:04:00,039 --> 02:04:02,189
to get round a corner.

1698
02:04:02,760 --> 02:04:04,478
The worse thing... Most of the cars

1699
02:04:04,560 --> 02:04:06,551
has the characteristic of one or the other,

1700
02:04:06,640 --> 02:04:09,313
but really bad cars had both.

1701
02:04:09,399 --> 02:04:12,836
And they change from one to the other in the blink of an eye

1702
02:04:12,960 --> 02:04:16,555
in the middle of a corner,
when you least want it to happen.

1703
02:04:16,680 --> 02:04:21,548
And that's very very disturbing for a driver,
because it destroys his faith

1704
02:04:21,680 --> 02:04:23,591
in the integrity of the car.

1705
02:04:23,680 --> 02:04:28,037
And that's absolutely crucial,
to particularly Formula One,

1706
02:04:28,520 --> 02:04:30,430
to developing,

1707
02:04:30,520 --> 02:04:34,832
for the driver to develop, that complete trust

1708
02:04:35,079 --> 02:04:38,435
in the car's temperament and behaviour.

1709
02:04:39,199 --> 02:04:41,270
And it was very clear in the beginning of the '94 season

1710
02:04:41,359 --> 02:04:43,475
that Williams absolutely did not have that.

1711
02:04:43,560 --> 02:04:47,439
It had the really unpleasant characteristic of changing its balance.

1712
02:04:49,119 --> 02:04:51,838
And that takes a lot of sorting out.

1713
02:04:52,359 --> 02:04:56,671
We say by the end of the season that Williams had sorted it out.

1714
02:04:57,199 --> 02:05:01,238
Damon Hill was winning races, challenging for the title.

1715
02:05:02,399 --> 02:05:05,789
And for the next season and the two seasons after that.

1716
02:05:05,880 --> 02:05:09,872
in '96 and '97,
Williams won the title again

1717
02:05:10,920 --> 02:05:13,114
because they had gone through that bad period.

1718
02:05:13,199 --> 02:05:16,033
But Senna's arrival
coincided with that period

1719
02:05:16,199 --> 02:05:21,479
and I think that was very... that was very disturbing to him

1720
02:05:21,560 --> 02:05:23,676
because he had gone there expecting something else.

1721
02:05:23,760 --> 02:05:27,832
